{
  "stem": "20088.6",
  "chunk_idx": 13,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "But my mother decided that, you know, there's no point staying there, and we will move into this-- into those barracks where the Nazis were staying.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "So we were there, and [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] we spent a few days like that, not really knowing what to do and just hoping the Germans wouldn't come back and the Russians weren't coming.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "And it was good, but it was terrible as well.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "And one day, my mother was hacking ice in the pond, and a lorry came.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 45,
      "text": "And me and the other people were in the house, because we didn't go out when it wasn't necessary.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 46,
      "text": "It was terribly cold.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 47,
      "text": "And we looked, and we saw it was Germans.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 48,
      "text": "And they said something to my mother, and I saw that she went with them, walked with them, and then they went into the camp.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 49,
      "text": "And they seemed to round up some more people who were still alive there, and who they tried to get out to walk.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 50,
      "text": "And they were coming back to take those people to walk still-- make more transport.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 51,
      "text": "And we watched petrified that they would come in and-- but we hid there, and they never came and looked in the house.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 52,
      "text": "But my mother, we-- we-- we saw then that she walked with them and went out of the camp.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 53,
      "text": "And a few hours later, she came back.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 54,
      "text": "It got dark then, and when they couldn't see so well, the Germans, she dropped dead-- she dropped down and pretended to be dead.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 55,
      "text": "And they left-- let her lie there and they walked away.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 56,
      "text": "And then she came back, so that was another moment where she-- where I thought, again, I had lost her.",
      "word_count": 20
    }
  ],
